WEBVTT

00:02.297 --> 00:03.897
Previously on This Is Us...

00:03.899 --> 00:05.899
You've always said that
you wanted to finish school.

00:05.901 --> 00:08.235
I think the time is now.

00:08.579 --> 00:11.701
Randall, it's a struggle for me
to get out of bed every morning.

00:11.930 --> 00:14.011
It takes every single ounce
of energy that I have,

00:14.013 --> 00:16.413
and then I have nothing left
for the rest of the day.

00:16.415 --> 00:17.540
Nothing.

00:17.565 --> 00:19.383
I take office in the next few weeks,

00:19.385 --> 00:20.818
and God only knows what kind of effect

00:20.820 --> 00:22.453
that's gonna have on my family.

00:22.540 --> 00:24.445
I'm ready to tell you
what I want to do next.

00:24.776 --> 00:26.203
I want to teach.

00:26.759 --> 00:29.921
Kevin is newly sober,
just like his father.

00:29.994 --> 00:31.828
And he's had a really tough year.

00:39.411 --> 00:43.296
Babe, I'm begging
you, please, just pick one.

00:44.477 --> 00:45.696
I'm gonna zoom in on that.

00:45.721 --> 00:48.157
- Did-did you just say "just pick one"?
- Stop.

00:48.182 --> 00:51.450
Jack, come on, I'm covered
in triplet spit-up. Stop.

00:51.462 --> 00:54.613
Bec, you realize that the camera
that we choose today

00:54.615 --> 00:56.982
is gonna document
the most important moments

00:56.984 --> 00:58.618
of our family's lives?

00:59.539 --> 01:01.739
You become a completely different person

01:01.741 --> 01:02.960
in this store. You know that, right?

01:02.985 --> 01:05.164
Yeah, I do. Radio Shack Jack.

01:06.579 --> 01:08.145
- Radio Shack Jack?
- Yeah.

01:08.147 --> 01:10.664
Well, maybe he can tell me
why we need a new video camera.

01:10.696 --> 01:13.022
Because the old one doesn't have sound.

01:13.336 --> 01:15.453
Okay? And there-there are
things happening

01:15.478 --> 01:18.781
in the Pearson house
that I think we should hear.

01:20.109 --> 01:21.906
Look, when we're old and gray

01:21.922 --> 01:23.671
and we don't remember
what we ate for breakfast,

01:23.696 --> 01:25.585
you're gonna be so happy
that we've got tapes

01:25.610 --> 01:28.171
of these three at their absolute cutest.

01:33.076 --> 01:34.578
Present moment excluded.

01:36.422 --> 01:37.803
- Should we... swap them?
- Yeah.

01:37.828 --> 01:38.961
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah.

01:39.729 --> 01:42.757
Come on, come on, come on.

01:47.820 --> 01:49.390
There you go, there you go.

01:49.415 --> 01:52.421
It's okay. Here, sweetie, look.
Here's your sister Kate.

01:52.499 --> 01:53.928
It's Kate right here.

01:55.014 --> 01:56.593
Hmm. Yeah.

01:57.251 --> 01:59.773
- It's crazy how they soothe each other.
- Yeah.

02:00.621 --> 02:02.413
Oh, I should've gotten that on tape.

02:05.663 --> 02:08.717
Customer needs assistance in aisle four.

02:09.088 --> 02:12.255
Customer needs assistance in aisle four.

02:19.289 --> 02:20.507
Rebecca?

02:21.023 --> 02:22.422
Hey, I thought that was you.

02:22.570 --> 02:24.584
Uh, Matt. Matt Dixon.

02:24.609 --> 02:26.029
Our kids went to middle school together?

02:26.054 --> 02:29.110
Oh. Yeah, hi, Matt.

02:29.135 --> 02:32.135
Hi. Yeah, you were the only,
uh, guy in the PTA.

02:32.160 --> 02:34.393
Yep. Yep. Comes with the
single-dad territory.

02:40.430 --> 02:41.545
You need some help?

02:41.547 --> 02:43.539
Actually, yes. Please, I...

02:43.564 --> 02:47.443
I-I need a new camera
for graduation tomorrow.

02:47.468 --> 02:50.428
Actually... I have two
graduations tomorrow.

02:50.453 --> 02:52.946
'Cause my other son Randall's
at a different school,

02:52.971 --> 02:55.976
and... he's valedictorian.

02:56.164 --> 02:58.319
Wow. Congratulations.

02:58.344 --> 02:59.546
Thank you.

03:00.661 --> 03:03.195
Let's see. Well, um...

03:03.898 --> 03:06.124
I mean, I have this one
right here, and I love it.

03:06.149 --> 03:08.163
Yeah, it has a-a flip-out monitor there

03:08.188 --> 03:09.898
and a really good digital zoom.

03:10.554 --> 03:13.023
I don't know what that means.

03:13.570 --> 03:17.242
Sorry, my husband, he used to...
handle all this stuff.

03:17.945 --> 03:19.265
Yeah.

03:19.977 --> 03:22.678
You know, I-I've been meaning
to reach out to you

03:22.680 --> 03:24.556
- ever since he...
- That's all right. Thanks.

03:25.654 --> 03:27.828
Uh... Okay.

03:28.195 --> 03:29.968
- Yeah, that looks good.
- All right.

03:31.125 --> 03:33.569
Um... well, it was very nice to see you.

03:33.594 --> 03:36.227
And I appreciate this recommendation.

03:36.392 --> 03:37.672
Thanks.

03:39.558 --> 03:40.843
Hey. Rebecca?

03:42.523 --> 03:44.452
Would you like to... I don't know...

03:44.711 --> 03:47.305
grab a cup of coffee
or something sometime?

03:49.859 --> 03:52.094
Or... you know, I-I shouldn't have...

03:53.000 --> 03:55.467
Uh, I-I'm... I'm gonna go pay.

03:56.109 --> 03:57.328
Yeah, okay.

